      "@context": "http://www.w3.org/ns/anno.jsonld",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "transcribing",
          "value": "WISDOM AND WONDER,\npassion and instruction,\nstory and symbol.\nAll these things,\nYour Torah gives to us.\nAnd the more we devote ourselves to it,\nthe more it grows and gives.\nWhat could be a truer token\nof Your abiding love\nthan this holiest of Your works,\nand the living language\nthat gives it form?\nבָּרוּךְ אַתָּה, יְיָ, אוֹהֵב עַמּוֹ יִשְׂרָאֵל.\nBaruch atah, Adonai, ohev amo Yisrael.",
          "language": "en"
        }
      ],
      "created": "2026-07-14T19:52:27.205Z",
